On 9/16/05 4:27 PM, "mark durrant" <markd89(-at-)yahoo.com> wrote:


> 3. I'm not sure where the gasket/washer goes. It's
> metal and has the 5 holes so I am assuming it must go
> between the flywheel and the engine. Right?

This goes under the big screws that hold the flywheel to the crankshaft. It
is like a lock washer, but is does all 5 screws at once.

Don't put it where you said or the crank endplay will get completely messed
up.


